n is considered a name of great virtue and generosity.\\\",\\\"spiritual_meaning\\\":\\\"In Hadith, Prophet Muhammad (pbuh) mentioned Zain as a name for those who strive to purify their intentions and actions, and give generously to others.\\\",\\\"emotional_traits\\\":[\\\"Kind\\\",\\\"Just\\\"],\\\"hidden_personality_traits\\\":[\\\"V\\\"],\\\"lucky_number\\\":3,\\\"lucky_day\\\":\\\"Thursday\\\",\\\"lucky_colors\\\":[\\\"#F7DC6F\\\",\\\"#E6B34D\\\",\\\"#F8B14D\\\"],\\\"lucky_stone\\\":\\\"Tiger Eye\\\",\\\"life_path_number\\\":5,\\\"numerology_meaning\\\":\\\"The name Zain is believed to have numerological significance, with a life path number of 5. This number is associated with the themes of adventure, change, and progress. People with this number are often seen as free spirits, and are drawn to new experiences and challenges. They are also natural communicators and problem solvers, and have a strong desire to explore and learn.\\\",\\\"in_arabic\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"زين\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"زين يعني الجمال والزينة في اللغة العربية\\\"},\\\"in_urdu\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"زین\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"زین کا مطلب خوبصورتی اور جمال ہے\\\"},\\\"in_hindi\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"ज़ैन\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"ज़ैन का अर्थ सुंदरता और सौंदर्य है\\\"},\\\"in_pashto\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"زین\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"زین د ښکلا او جمال معنی لري\\\"},\\\"in_english\\\":{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Zain\\\",\\\"meaning\\\":\\\"beauty, adornment, or handsome\\\"},\\\"pronunciation\\\":{\\\"english\\\":\\\"ZAYN\\\",\\\"ipa\\\":\\\"/ˈzæɪn/\\\"},\\\"celebrity_usage\\\":[\\\"Zain Jabarah Al-Abidin\\\",\\\"Zain Malik\\\",\\\"Zain al-Abidin (son of Imam Hussein)\\\"],\\\"social_tags\\\":[\\\"#ZainMeaning\\\",\\\"#IslamicBabyNames\\\",\\\"#ArabicNames\\\",\\\"#MuslimNames\\\",\\\"#Zain\\\"],\\\"name_variations\\\":[],\\\"popularity_score\\\":78,\\\"popularity_by_region\\\":[{\\\"region\\\":\\\"Saudi Arabia\\\",\\\"country_code\\\":\\\"SA\\\",\\\"score\\\":78,\\\"year\\\":2024},{\\\"region\\\":\\\"Pakistan\\\",\\\"country_code\\\":\\\"PK\\\",\\\"score\\\":71,\\\"year\\\":2024},{\\\"region\\\":\\\"UAE\\\",\\\"country_code\\\":\\\"AE\\\",\\\"score\\\":70,\\\"year\\\":2024}],\\\"seo\\\":{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Zain Name Meaning | Islam Baby Names 2026\\\",\\\"meta_description\\\":\\\"Discover the complete meaning of Zain, a beautiful Islam name meaning \\\\\\\"Giver of good\\\\\\\". Learn about its Arabic origin and spiritual significance.\\\",\\\"meta_keywords\\\":\\\"Zain, Islam name, baby names, Giver of good, Islam baby names, name meaning\\\",\\\"description_paragraph\\\":\\\"Zain is a meaningful Islam name of Arabic origin that means \\\\\\\"Giver of good\\\\\\\". Derived from the Arabic root 'z-n-y', meaning 'to give' or 'to support'. In Islamic tradition, Zain is considered a name of great virtue and generosity.\\\",\\\"keywords\\\":[\\\"Zain\\\",\\\"Islam name\\\",\\\"baby names\\\",\\\"Giver of good\\\",\\\"Islam tradition\\\",\\\"Arabic origin\\\"],\\\"faq\\\":[{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What is the meaning of Zain in Islam tradition?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Zain is a beautiful Islam name meaning \\\\\\\"Giver of good\\\\\\\". This name has deep spiritual significance in Islam tradition.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"Is Zain a good Islam name for a baby?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Yes, Zain is an excellent Islam name choice. It carries positive meanings and cultural significance.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What is the origin of the name Zain?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"The name Zain has Arabic origins and is deeply rooted in Islam tradition.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"How do you pronounce Zain correctly?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Zain is pronounced ZAYN in English.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"What are the spiritual benefits of naming a child Zain?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Naming a child Zain brings blessings. The meaning \\\\\\\"Giver of good\\\\\\\" inspires positive qualities.\\\"},{\\\"q\\\":\\\"How popular is the name Zain?\\\",\\\"a\\\":\\\"Zain is very popular in Islam communities worldwide.\\\"}],\\\"seo_score\\\":96,\\\"focus_keyword\\\":\\\"Zain meaning\\\",\\\"secondary_keywords\\\":[\\\"Islam name Zain\\\",\\\"Zain meaning\\\",\\\"Zain origin\\\"]},\\\"monetization\\\":{\\\"propush_trigger\\\":true,\\\"exit_ad_enabled\\\":true,\\\"ads_enabled\\\":true},\\\"cultural_impact\\\":\\\"The name Zain carries a rich cultural heritage, recognized and respected among various Islamic communities. It signifies qualities of leadership, strength, and resilience, dating back to the days of early Islamic history where prominent figures bearing the name Zain, such as Zain al-Abidin, the fourth Shia Imam, held important spiritual and political roles.\\\",\\\"spiritual_significance\\\":\\\"Spiritually, the name Zain is deeply steeped in the treasured values of kindness, generosity, and selflessness. As such, the personality of those named Zain is seen as a reflection of God's immense generosity and benevolence towards humankind, inviting them to emulate these beautiful qualities in their daily lives.\\\",\\\"islamic_reference\\\":{\\\"is_quranic\\\":false,\\\"note\\\":\\\"Traditional Islamic name with deep spiritual significance in Islamic culture\\\"},\\\"historical_references\\\":[{\\\"reference\\\":\\\"Historical records show that Zain is mentioned in the book 'The Thousand and One Nights' The name Zain carried significant weight in that era.\\\",\\\"time_period\\\":\\\"18th century\\\",\\\"context\\\":\\\"The name Zain is associated with the Arabic word for 'blessing' or 'prosperity'\\\"}],\\\"modern_usage\\\":{\\\"trends\\\":[\\\"increasingly popular in the US and UK\\\"],\\\"platforms\\\":[\\\"social media, literature\\\"],\\\"modern_context\\\":\\\"The name Zain remains relevant in modern Muslim society, representing a bridge between traditional Islamic values and contemporary life. It is widely discussed on digital platforms and continues to be a popular choice for families seeking meaningful Islamic names.\\\"},\\\"name_in_real_life\\\":{\\\"person_name\\\":\\\"Khalid Zain\\\",\\\"location\\\":\